 Trump escaped criticism for stiff-arming national reporters; they defended=
 the campaign=E2=80=99s podcast strategy and their push to line up endorsem=
ents from Hollywood celebrities and musicians; they explained their view th=
at they needed to win over moderates and Trump-skeptical Republicans by clo=
sing with a =E2=80=9Csave democracy=E2=80=9D argument and campaign events w=
ith <b>Liz Cheney</b>. Plouffe repeatedly stressed that the fundamental cur=
rents of the election=E2=80=94tough economic headwinds and a generally sour=
 national mood=E2=80=94were too difficult to overcome. <br/></td>
